title: Strictly's Catherine Tyldesley grabs a coffee en route to rehearsals to practice the Tango
text:
Catherine Tyldesley ensured she got her caffeine kick as she headed to Strictly rehearsals in Manchester on Wednesday.

The former Coronation Street actress, 36, appeared in high spirits as she grabbed a coffee for herself and dance partner Johannes Radebe ahead of getting to the studios.

Catherine and Johannes will dance the Tango to Annie Lennox Little Bird for week five of the competition.

Coffee run: Catherine Tyldesley ensured she got her caffeine kick as she headed to Strictly rehearsals in Manchester on Wednesday

Catherine cut a sporty figure in tight black leggings, a plain T-shirt and leather jacket.

Opting for comfort with pink Nike trainers, the actress certainly didn't travel light as she toted a large bumblebee bag, rucksand and shrugged a £805 Gucci Marmont bag over her shoulder.

The former soap star wore her brunette locks in a glamorous curls and accentuated her bronzed complexion with a full face of make-up.

Groovy: The former Coronation Street actress, 36, appeared in high spirits as she grabbed a coffee for herself and dance partner Johannes Radebe ahead of getting to the studios

Last week, Catherine and Johannes danced the Charleston to Single Ladies by Beyoncé.

The duo got one step closer to the Strictly glitterball as they flew through to week five of the competition, securing a healthy 30 points out of 40.

There are now 12 couples left competing on the BBC Latin and ballroom show.

Keep dancing! Catherine cut a sporty figure in tight black leggings, a plain T-shirt and leather jacket

Karim Zeroual and Amy Dowden, who topped the leaderboard on Saturday with a score of 38, will perform a salsa to Baha Men's classic hit Who Let The Dogs Out.

While they found themselves at the summit over the weekend, it was former Emmerdale actor Kelvin Fletcher and his pro partner Oti Mabuse who 'broke' the judges with their racy Rumba

The pair sent pulses-racing with the sensual performance, but this Saturday they'll face a very different challenge as they tackle the Cha Cha to Aston Merrygold's track Get Stupid.

Strike a pose! The soap star couldn't resist taking a cheeky Instagram selfie ahead of rehearsals

Retired footballer Alex Scott avoided the cut on the last show despite finishing bottom of the leaderboard with just 23, and she'll look to bounce back as she and Neil Jones deliver a Charleston to Pump Up The Jam by Swingrowers.

Emma Barton and Anton du Beke will dance the Paso Doble to Mark Ronson and Miley Cyrus' collaboration Nothing Breaks Like A Heart.

Viewers will also get to hear Jump On It by the Sugarhill Gang this weekend when Mike Bushell and Katya Jones perform the Samba, and Chris Ramsey will Quickstep onto the dancefloor with Karen Hauer to Let's Go Crazy by Prince.

Model Emma Weymouth and her pro partner Aljaž Skorjanec's routine this week will be the Viennese Waltz set to Whitney Houston's Saving All My Love For You, and Michelle Visage and Giovanni Pernice are set to deliver a Rumba to Too Good At Goodbyes by Sam Smith.

Saffron Baker and AJ Pritchard will channel Frank Sinatra and dance the Foxtrot to the theme from New York, New York, with David James and Nadiya Bychkova setting their Jive to Michael Buble's Such A Night.

Finally, this week's Couples' Choice wil see Will Bayley and Janette Manrara show off their moves to Lukas Graham's tune 7 Years.

Success: Last week, Catherine and Johannes danced the Charleston to Single Ladies by Beyoncé and got 30 points out of 40
